HEADWORD: Oreosoma
<hw>O`re*o*so"ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
from Gr. <grk>'o`ros</grk>, <grk>-eos</grk>, mountain + <grk>sw^ma</grk>
body.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of small oceanic fishes,
remarkable for the large conical tubercles which cover the under
surface.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

